properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued March 1 at 11:20PM MST until March 2 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...OCCASIONAL LIGHT SNOW WITH PATCHY BLOWING SNOW WILL CONTINUE
THROUGH EARLY MONDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Snow and patchy blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations
of up to one inch. Winds gusting up to 25 mph.

* WHERE...Central Carbon County, North Snowy Range Foothills,
Sierra Madre and Snowy Mountain Ranges.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and poor driving
conditions in falling and blowing snow.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST MONDAY... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
